<div class="well">
  <form method="GET" action="/">
    <div class="form-group">
    <label for="exampleInputEmail1">Enter CSS URL</label>
      <input type="text" name="cssURL" class="form-control" id="exampleInputEmail1"  value="https://maxcdn.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.3.4/css/bootstrap.css">
    </div>
    <div class="form-group">
      <label for="exampleInputPassword1">Enter Namespace</label>
      <input type="text" name="ns" class="form-control" id="exampleInputPassword1" value="mynamespace">
    </div>
    <button type="submit" class="btn btn-success text-center">Submit</button>
  </form>
</div>

 
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-6">
   <b> INPUT: </b>     
<pre><code class='css'>
.redClass{
  color: red;
}
.blueClass {
  color: blue;
}
</code></pre>
</div>
 <div class="col-md-6"> 
 <b> OUTPUT:</b>   
<pre><code class='css'>
.mynamespace .redClass{
  color: red;
}
.mynamespace .blueClass {
  color: blue;
}
</code></pre>
</div>
</div>

<div>
<br>
<br>
<h3>USAGE:</h3>
<p>1. Enter some namespace and a CSS URL and then press Submit.
<p>2. Result will be displayed in the browser. Simply save the result (cmd +s or ctrl +s) from the browser</p>
<p>3. Wrap your components within a div with the <b>mynamespace</b> class</p>
<pre><code class='html'>
&lt;div class=&#39;mynamespace&#39;&gt;
  &lt;component1 attribute=&#39;value&#39;/&gt;
